### Title Gradient Treatment

Headlines use a vertical gradient from bright to slightly muted:

**Gold titles (H1, H2 on dark backgrounds):**
```css
.title-gradient-gold {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #F7D063 0%, #F2DE9B 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}
```

**Light titles (alternative):**
```css
.title-gradient-light {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, #FFFFFF 0%, #F5F4F3 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}
```

## Components

### CTA Buttons â€” 3D Beveled Style

Primary CTAs use inner gradients and a subtle outer rim to create a convex/pillow effect.

**Primary CTA (gold):**
- Fill: `linear-gradient(180deg, #F2DE9B 0%, #F7D063 100%)` â€” lighter at top creates convex illusion
- Border: `1px solid rgba(245, 244, 243, 0.25)`
- Box shadow: `inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.15)`
- Text: Carbon Black `#1A1B17` in Sora Bold
- Border radius: `9999px` (pill) or `12px` (rounded rect)

**Hover state:**
- Intensify gradient brightness slightly
- Add outer glow: `0 0 20px rgba(247, 208, 99, 0.3)`

**Secondary CTA (outline/ghost):**
- Fill: transparent
- Border: `1px solid #F7D063`
- Text: Royal Gold `#F7D063`
- Hover: subtle gold background at 10% opacity

**Disabled state:**
- Reduce opacity to 50%
- Remove hover effects

