Use Tailwind default spacing scale (4px base unit). Key usage:
- Section padding: `py-16` to `py-24` (64â€“96px)
- Card padding: `p-6` to `p-8` (24â€“32px)
- Component gaps: `gap-4` to `gap-6` (16â€“24px)
- Text block spacing: `space-y-4` (16px)

### Container Widths

- Max content width: `1280px` (`max-w-6xl`)
- Wide sections: `1440px` (`max-w-7xl`)
- Narrow content (blog, legal): `768px` (`max-w-3xl`)

## Accessibility

### Contrast Requirements

All text must meet WCAG 2.1 AA minimum contrast ratios:
- Normal text: 4.5:1
- Large text (18px+ or 14px+ bold): 3:1

Verified combinations:
- White Smoke `#F5F4F3` on Carbon Black `#1A1B17`: ~15:1 âś“
- Royal Gold `#F7D063` on Carbon Black `#1A1B17`: ~10:1 âś“
- Carbon Black `#1A1B17` on Royal Gold `#F7D063`: ~10:1 âś“

### Focus States

All interactive elements must have visible focus indicators:
- Use `--ring` color (`#F7D063`) for focus rings
- Minimum 3px ring width with offset
- Never remove focus outlines without replacement

## Do / Don't

### Do

- Use gold gradients sparingly on key headlines and primary CTAs
- Keep ambient background glows subtle (< 10% opacity)
- Maintain high contrast for body text (White Smoke on Carbon Black)
- Reserve 3D-beveled style for primary action buttons
- Use Sora ExtraBold only for H1/H2 headlines
- Apply consistent border radius within component families

### Don't

- Apply gold gradients to all text or body copy
- Create harsh, high-opacity color transitions
- Use gold colors for body text
- Apply bevel effect to secondary or ghost buttons
- Use ExtraBold weight for subheadings or body
- Mix pill and rounded-rect radius in the same context
- Remove focus indicators without accessible alternatives

## Implementation Notes

- Font loading: Use `next/font` for Sora and Geist with `display: swap`
- Gradient text: Always include fallback solid color for older browsers
- Dark mode: This is a dark-first design; no light mode variant planned for Phase 1
- Motion: Keep transitions subtle (150â€“200ms ease) to maintain premium feel
